<TEXT>
teachers in sacramento calif went on strike tuesday after 
contract talks broke down raising the number of students without 
classes to more than 110000 
in coeur dalene idaho teachers overwhelmingly ratified a new 
twoyear contract with the school board ending the threat of a 
strike set for tuesday 
walkouts in 12 districts in illinois michigan montana ohio and 
pennsylvania affected about 66000 students as of labor day 
negotiators worked through the holiday to try to head off a 
strike in sacramento with 48000 students the biggest district in 
the nation to have a walkout 
talks broke down about 3 am and teachers were on strike by 7 
am officials said the teachers want a 127 percent raise this 
year and are seeking classsize limitations and hiring deadlines for 
new teachers 
elsewhere in california teachers without a contract for 14 
months embraced a lastminute deal so schools could open tuesday in 
san jose the states thirdlargest city details of the agreement 
were not released 
in pennsylvania 378 teachers were on strike in three districts 
with 5700 students 
strikes began tuesday in two of those districts but a walkout 
that began in a fourth district perkiomen valley near philadelphia 
with 2300 students and 159 teachers ended in a settlement later in 
the day 
in the upper st clair school district in suburban pittsburgh an 
allday negotiating session monday settled a strike by 225 teachers 
and 3700 students went back to school tuesday teachers in the 
union school district in western pennsylvania returned to work on a 
daily basis 
in massachusetts the 317 teachers in the boston suburb of 
everett voted unanimously to go on strike in the second walkout in 
three years 
weve never had that anywhere in massachusetts said 
massachusetts teachers association spokesman stephen wollmer 
the district which has 3900 students had been scheduled to 
reopen wednesday 
teachers in nearby chelsea agreed to an unusual sixmonth 
contract with boston university which is administering the 
3500pupil school system in an experiment aimed at improving the 
troubled schools the teachers union said it agreed to the short 
contract to give the university time to raise money 
with school scheduled to start over the next 10 days talks 
continued with 28 other locals across the state 
schools in the great falls district in montana reopened tuesday 
with 540 substitute teachers for 12500 students only 45 of 723 
teachers showed up for work there last week salaries top the list 
of contract issues 
laurel mont teachers voted saturday to accept a contract 
giving them a 25 percent raise and returned to work tuesday 
in michigan teachers in the jackson and saginaw township school 
districts were on strike tuesday 
in ohio no negotiations were held in the indian creek and warren 
school districts in illinois pay negotiations continued as a 
strike in quincy entered a second week 
</TEXT>
