for sale 29000 home lots two 18hole 
golf courses a 1700seat auditorium a building supply store a 
121room hotel with restaurant and a weekly newspaper 
federal bank regulators are looking for a buyer for the 
development company that owns more than 10 percent of this onelight 
towns land and nearly all of the major recreation and public 
facilities 
land resources corp which came under federal control in may is 
among the more curious jetsam of the nations savings and loan 
crisis which has coughed up other odd thrift holdings from llamas 
to a desert bordello 
land resources was acquired in 1984 by security savings and loan 
of scottsdale ariz when the thrift was declared insolvent this 
year regulators seized its assets 
its strange for sure said william crocker appointed by the 
federal deposit insurance corp to oversee security savings which 
had about 1 billion in assets many sampls had real estate but to 
own part of a town is really unusual 
crocker said 60 to 80 information packets were being sent to 
potential bidders around the world and a deal should be completed 
before christmas he said only that the property is valued in the 
eight figures 
meanwhile residents of this 25yearold community are looking 
for assurances that life will continue as always amid the 
sprinklerfed lawns and bicycles leaning unlocked against evenly 
spaced palms on the edge of the everglades 
the one thing i keep repeating is dont worry nothing is 
going to change but as soon as they hear the federal government is 
involved they panic said carl strunk president of land resources 
corp 
although land resources has sold many of its former holdings 
including two shopping centers and a bowling alley it remains the 
largest employer of the towns 25000 residents 
strunk predicts land resources will be purchased by an 
development company interested in maintaining operations im 
convinced the whole of this company is worth more than the sum of 
its parts he said 
lehigh acres was ranch land before the postwar development boom 
land resources acquired the property in 1968 
original plans were for a retirement haven for northerners in 
one section targeted for retired telephone employees streets bear 
names such as switchboard and long lines 
other sections are typical smalltown america churches banks a 
small hospital two chinese restaurants and an industrial park 
strunk said lehigh acres has the potential for about 400000 
residents 
lehigh acres is growing by about 1000 residents annually and 
land resources brings families down for subsidized vacations to tour 
the community and timeshare units 
less than half the residents are retirees with the others mostly 
commuting to fort myers 12 miles away said strunk were just 
like any small town anywhere he said it just happens that a 
failed sampl owned part of it 
but word of the federal takeover is a tender subject 
in july strunk wrote a frontpage article in the companyowned 
lehigh times newspaper to allay concern about the sale strunk also 
has discouraged the nearly 500 land resources employees from 
discussing the sale with reporters 
this place is mr and mrs middle america its dayton ohio 
and detroit mich they are going to spend a lot of time worrying 
about this if people keep sounding alarmed said strunk i keep 
saying its not a big deal 
at the k mart lunch counter residents seemed more concerned with 
gossip than speculation on the fate of land resources 
this town will survive said joseph ferrante a retired new 
york police officer at worst maybe a new owner over there will 
be good it could be a change for the better 
</TEXT>
