<TEXT>
the whoosh and boom of exploding 
rockets terrorizes kabul at all hours of the day and night creating 
a climate of fear not known before in the 11yearold afghan civil 
war 
periods of intense rocketing occurred in the past especially 
last fall but longtime observers say the barrage that began in june 
has been more deadly 
between june 25 and aug 26 united nations sources said 577 
rockets pounded kabul killing 366 people and injuring 999 nearly 
all were civilians struck at random in homes or offices at bus 
stops bazaars movie houses 
we are very very afraid that rockets will kill all the 
