under usdas price support program 
average cotton yields are forecast at 595 pounds per acre on the 
average down 4 percent from last year yields in the delta and 
southwest are expected to be down 14 percent and 19 percent 
respectively because of bad weather 
the total 198990 cotton supply is forecast at 19 million bales 
for the marketing year that began aug 1 
allowing for domestic use and exports the us cotton inventory 
by aug 1 1990 could be pulled down to around 39 million bales 
from an aug 1 carryover this year of 75 million bales the report 
said 
although us cotton textile imports are expected to reach 
nearrecord levels and manmade fiber prices have become more 
competitive with cotton domestic mills will likely use 77 million 
bales during 198990 the report said lower textile inventories 
and larger denim production should keep domestic mill consumption 
strong this season 
domestic cotton use may rise to and average of 23 pounds per 
capita up two pounds from last year the report said 
