raised by the death june 3 of ayatollah ruhollah khomeini irans 
revolutionary patriarch and the election to the presidency july 28 
of hashemi rafsanjani leader of the pragmatist faction that 
supports closer ties with the west 
because of the closed nature of iranian politics it is difficult 
to assess whether the besharati comments signaled a new willingness 
to negotiate freedom for the hostages 
last month rafsanjani offered to help work for their release if 
the united states adopted a friendlier policy toward iran and he 
cited frozen iranian assets as one sore point 
in an apparent struggle between radical and pragmatist factions 
within the iranian government ayatollah ali khamenei irans 
spiritual leader said aug 14 that there would be no dealings with 
the united states but foreign minister ali akbar velayati on the 
same day left open the possibility 
the day before irna outlined conditions for release of the 
hostages citing the assets 
an iranian newspaper kayhan international said aug 15 that 
unfreezing the assets would not guarantee iranian help in freeing 
the hostages 
the next day it said the united states can only improve its ties 
with iran by releasing the assets 
besharati has made several trips to lebanon in recent years and 
is believed to have influence with hezbollah or party of god the 
proiranian group believed to sponsor shiite kidnap gangs 
in an interview published today in the washington post sheik 
