reports of the disaster had appeared in the official iraqi news 
media 
the london newspaper quoted us diplomats as saying they had 
received information from iraqi sources of a major incident in the 
second half of august in which the casualty toll numbered in the low 
hundreds 
but it quoted unspecified sources as saying that 700 bodies had 
been recovered it quoted the other sources as saying the blast 
destroyed a third of the huge center which contained workers 
housing as well as armament factories 
the paper said there was no immediate suggestion of sabotage 
the casualties appear to have included egyptian military and 
