million speculation was rife tuesday that billionaire oilman marvin 
davis who previously made a lower bid may seek help from another 
foreign airline to top the groups offer 
british airways role in the ual bid is similar to that played by 
klm which is the foreign partner in the investor group that 
recently paid 365 billion for northwest airlines parent nwa inc 
in a leveraged buyout 
under us law foreign airlines may not own more than 25 percent 
of a domestic carrier and the department of transportation can 
object to smaller stakes if it believes the foreign company is 
trying to exert control 
assistant transportation secretary jeffrey n shane said last 
week that the department is reluctant to approve such foreign 
purchases partly because there still are many questions about us 
airlines access to european markets after the common markets 
