camp as saying davis was talking with european and noneuropean 
carriers 
the davis group did not return telephone calls seeking 
confirmation of the report 
davis previously indicated he might increase his bid to acquire 
united the nations secondlargest airline 
the bid by the labormanagement alliance has financial backing 
from british airways plc 
if successful the labormanagement groups plan would result in 
75 percent employee ownership making ual the countrys largest 
workerowned company british airways would own 15 percent of the 
company and uals management led by chairman stephen wolf would 
hold 10 percent 
federal aviation regulators reportedly are concerned with the 
involvement of foreign entities in takeovers of us airlines 
government authorities are expected to closely examine proposed 
acquisitions that include nonus backers 
