spy the irreverant new york humor magazine can 
distribute its spoof of cliffs notes the longestablished study 
guide to the classics a federal appeals panel ruled tuesday 
three judges of the 2nd us circuit court of appeals vacated a 
lower courts injunction that banned the distribution of spy notes 
a parody that used the cliffs notes format to also poke fun at what 
spy coeditor kurt andersen called the hip urban novel 
the onepage ruling did not give the reasons for the decision 
the judges said a full opinion would follow 
it is a happy day for us and the first amendment andersen 
said 
